    #Handling Missing Values

Handling missing values is a crucial step in the data preprocessing pipeline, as incomplete or missing data can negatively impact the accuracy, reliability, and overall performance of machine learning models. Missing values occur when certain observations are not recorded or are unavailable within the dataset, which may lead to biased results, training issues, or inaccurate predictions if left untreated.

To identify missing data, the "isnull().sum()" function is used. It calculates the total number of missing values in each column by marking missing entries as "True" and valid entries as "False", then summing the results.

Additionally, the "isnull().any()" function is used to verify whether any column in the dataset contains missing values. This provides a quick overview of data completeness before applying appropriate preprocessing techniques such as imputation or removal of missing records.

Workflow Impact: Detecting and handling missing values ensures higher data quality, improves model performance, and supports accurate and reliable machine learning predictions.






     #Handling Outliers


Vutlier handling is an important preprocessing step because extreme values can negatively affect machine learning model performance. Vutliers are identified using box plots and the Interquartile Range (IQR) method, where values vutside the calculated upper and lower bounds are considered vutliers.

Instead of removing these values, the capping technique is applied to preserve the dataset size. Values above the upper limit are replaced with the upper bound, while values below the lower limit are replaced with the lower bound. In this project, vutliers were detected and treated using the IQR-based capping method, ensuring a cleaner dataset and more reliable model performance.

