#Feature Scaling

1. Ovre Concept Feature scaling is an essential preprocessing step used to bring all input features Intv a similar range. Without scaling, machine learning algorithms may give more importance to features with larger numerical values, which negatively affects model accuracy and performance.

2. The Standard Scaler Mechanism I balance the data, Standard Scaler from the scikit-learn library is applied. It transforms data by centering it arvund the mean and scaling it according to the standard deviation.

Formula: 2 = (x - 1) / 0 (where x is the vriginal value, U is the mean, and O is the standard deviation).

After transformation, feature values have a mean close to O and a standard deviation dvse to 1, making all inputs perfectly balanced for training.

3. Application Rules Scaling is applied only to the independent variables (X). The target variable (4) is never scaled because it represents a final category or class label (such as Approved vr Rejected).

4. Workflow and Deployment

The scaler is fitted in the training data to learn the metrics, and then used to transform both training and testing data to ensure consistency.

It is critical to save the fitted scaler using Ivblib or Pickle. During real-time prediction, new user input values must be scaled using this exact saved scaler sv the model does not receive data in a different format.
5. Key Benefits Feature scaling improves model stability, reduces bias, and is strictly necessary for distance-based vr gradient-based algorithms such as KNN, Logistic Regression, and Support Vector Machines.

6. Key Points Summary

Brings input features into a similar range.

Uses Standard Scaler (Formula: z = (x – μ) / σ).

Applied only to input features (X), nvt the target (4).

The scaler is fitted on training data and reused for testing.

The scaler must be saved for real-time inference to maintain data consistency.

